snmp --> udp 161,161 --> For Monitoring and Management
HP open view, cisco works, PRTG, IBM neusecure, cacti

For Routers & Switches:

#snmp-server community CCNA           !--> the Important command (like a password bet the zabbix server and the switch)
#snmp-server location First_floor     !--> for showing off
#snmp-server contact ahmed            !--> for showing off
#snmp-server host 10.0.0.1 version 2c CCNA 

Another Way:
#snmp-server enable traps

---------------------------------------------------------
snmp version 3
On Routers:
#snmp-server group group1 v3 priv !-->supports authentican and privacy (encryption)
#snmp-server user user1 group1 v3 auth sha auth_pass priv aes 128 encryption_pass
#snmp-server enable traps 

#show run
#show snmp user









